            <creation>This story, with the short title "A Bitter Servant's Suicide Reversed," is recent: the earliest PEMM manuscript* in which this story appears is from around<date>1881</date>.Originally composed in <placeName ref="LOC3010Ethiop">Ethiopia</placeName></creation>
            <abstract>
                <p>A certain servant hated the man to whom he'd been entrusted. Intending to frame his trustee and get him arrested, the servant slit his own throat and died. When the trustee found the servant's corpse, he prayed for Mary to revive him, which she did. The resuscitated servant then publicly admitted that he'd died by suicide.</p>
